1 medical science from Utah State University in 1989, and a doctor of humane letters from
2 Snow College in 1994; and
3 WHEREAS, President Nelson was an exceptional cardiothoracic surgeon, and he and
4 other medical professionals pioneered the development of the heart-lung machine; in 1955,
5 he became the first doctor in the state of Utah to perform open-heart surgery; and
6 WHEREAS, President Nelson authored numerous publications and chapters in
7 medical textbooks and lectured and visited professionally throughout the United States and
8 internationally; he received many awards and honors throughout his life, including the Heart
9 of Gold Award from the American Heart Association, the Golden Plate Award presented by
10 the American Academy of Achievement, and the Gandhi-King-Mandela Peace Prize; and
11 WHEREAS, President Nelson served as president of the Society for Vascular
12 Surgery, a director of the American Board of Thoracic Surgery, chairman of the Council of
13 Cardiovascular Surgery for the American Heart Association, and president of the Utah State
14 Medical Association; and
15 WHEREAS, President Nelson developed close ties with China during his career and
16 was credited with introducing open-heart surgery to China in 1980; he was awarded
17 honorary professorships from three universities in the People's Republic of China; and
18 WHEREAS, President Nelson notably performed open-heart surgery on Spencer W.
19 Kimball, who went on to serve as the twelfth president of the Church; and
20 WHEREAS, during his career, President Nelson served in various church callings,
21 including stake president of the Bonneville Stake, general president of the Sunday School,
22 regional representative for Brigham Young University, and regional representative for the
23 Kearns Utah Region; and
24 WHEREAS, President Nelson accepted the call to serve as a member of the Quorum
25 of the Twelve Apostles and began serving on April 7, 1984; over nearly thirty-four years of
26 service in the Quorum, he visited one hundred thirty-four countries to share the gospel; and
27 WHEREAS, President Nelson served as the president of the Quorum of Twelve
28 Apostles from July 15, 2015, until he was called to lead the church; he was made the
29 seventeenth president of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints on January 14, 2018,
30 shortly after the passing of President Thomas S. Monson; and
