1 WHEREAS, during his presidency, President Nelson announced two hundred
2 temples, which is the most of any leader of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints;
3 he also presided over a historic number of large-scale changes in the church and led its
4 members through the COVID-19 pandemic; and
5 WHEREAS, President Nelson is survived by his wife, Wendy Watson Nelson; eight
6 children; and more than two hundred grandchildren and great-grandchildren; he will be
7 deeply missed, but the legacy of his dedicated service to the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter
8 Day Saints shall live on in the hearts and minds of those who were privileged to have known
9 him.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
11 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of Russell
12 M. Nelson, president of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints; does hereby
13 recognize his enduring legacy as a pioneer in the field of cardiothoracic surgery and as a
14 leader in the Mormon community; and does hereby extend sincere wishes that his family,
15 friends, and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of his beautiful life.
